rComments: She was a tough grader for our projects- AVOID. She made our MENTAL HEALTH class be a burden on my mental health. Did not enjoy what I thought would be a fun and interesting class. That being said, exams are pretty easy but the project (worth 35%) was absolutely insane.

avoid for online classes. She did pre record the lecture which was great, but she does a poor job of actually explaining the course material and her slides lack detail as well. In addition, I did not appreciate the fact that she took advantage of online classes & continued to post lectures, that were expected to be done, during reading week.

Im sure all the positive ratings were published here by herself. This teacher is awful!! Half the class has anxiety problems now because of her. Exams are ridiculous! She asks tiny details about things she hardly went over. She also made us study several units at home because she was « sick ». You cant test students on stuff you didnt teach

Anne Konkle is the worst teacher I have had in 4 years at university. I have never seen exams so poorly representitive of the material. She has no idea what she is teaching. She feels embarrased during the classes because she gets all mixed up and goes to read her notes. She is so unfair and suggests you to drop the course and throw away 1000$

Nice prof but the exams demolish you. I took this class only taking in account her rating but because the exams are so tough, I would never retake anything with Konkle. I attended just to help retain the info for exams. She does not give hints, just explains diagrams and stuff. You could pass the class without going to class and studying hard.
She will ask questions of medication name we never studied in class

Midterm was extremely unfair, we were expected to know tiny details. The rest of the grading was GROUP projects (even the final). Feel like I didn't learn anything in the class, because stopped having lectures halfway through. I would never take this prof again.

Professor really cares about us connecting the content to ourselves in some way! There is a midterm, a solo paper, a group final paper (instead of exam), and a group presentation. The papers and presentation are doable and not hard! She is helpful if you approach her! She does not negotiate marks though. Midterm was fair, textbook was not required.

Premièrement, elle donne 2 heures de théories (lecture de ses diapos) sans pause donc à la fin, la concentration n'y est plus. Elle ne répond pas aux questions en classe si ça a trait à la matière préalablement enseignée. Elle ne dit jamais ce qui sera sur l'examen et elle prend un temps incroyable à corriger! Ses examens sont faciles par contre!

Bonne prof mais cours très difficile ... J'ai mis plus d'effort dans ce cours que n'importe quel et j'ai quand même eu beaucoup de difficulté. Il y a beaucoup de matières mais peu de celle-ci se retrouve sur l'examen. Difficile à se retrouver dans les A.
Extremely nice lady and very helpful, but her classes are tough. You need to put in a lot of effort to break into the A's spectrum.

She's an amazing prof, loved her for 4324! The course has an oral presentation, participation marks, a term paper instead of a final, and one midterm. She marks hard for the paper and the midterm requires a lot of memorization, but considering there is no final it's not too bad of a course load. She gives very good feedback as well!

As a person, she was really nice. Classes were interesting. However, I pretty much died in her exams. Normally,   I would consider myself to be a pretty good student. But, there was just someone about her exams that just doesn't work for me even when I've studied.
Anne est très gentille et passionnée pour sa matière, mais il y a énormément de matière et ses examens sont trop longs..

She was very easy to understand, examples given were fairly reflected in the midterms and final exam. People in the class said she went too fast, but these were people who didn't know how to read simple coordinates on a line graph.
Bonne professeure. Elle est bien organiser et enseigne bien la matiere

Look I hate her with a passion but that's because she's a snake who wouldn't increase my grade because I was .3% short... She's a good lecturer, her exams were fair however she corrected very strictly and she always had time for her students. And yea the textbook is completely useless.

Worst prof that I have had so far. She never give hints on the exams - which are too long to actually finish. Don't bother attending this class as you will learn more from reading the textbook - got a C by doing so. Avoid if at all possible.

She takes a long time to mark midterms and then did not even post the marks before the final exam. Midterms were impossible to finish because they were way too long. They did not represent what was taught in the lectures. She doesn't even use the assigned text book.

Terrible prof! Rushes through slides, does not explain material well. Midterms are extremely long and there isn't sufficient time provided to finish all the questions. She comes off as a snob. Refuses to answer people's questions during midterms. Only answers VC questions if there is an exam the next day. Does not give ANY hints prior to exams.
The exams are ridicously hard! the question are usually about subject she never talked in class! She do not explain well!!! If you can avoid her....DO IT!!!!

Bonne professeure.  Elle est passionnée de la matière qu'elle enseigne mais a parfois de la difficulté à garder l'attention des étudiants.  A améliorer: distinguer ce qui est matière à examen et non.  Autrement, c'est une excellente prof qui donne de très bons conseils quand on lui consulte un à un! Très gentille! Un bon semestre.
